author: William Hughes
title: Newswire: The SXSW Comedy line-up offers up HarmonQuest and an evening with Bob Odenkirk
text:
Share Tweet 
The SXSW Comedy Festival has released the schedule for its upcoming slate of shows, the tenth since the week-long event grew out of a single night of comedy back in 2008. This year’s line-up is heavy on programs based on current and upcoming TV and streaming shows, with Seeso’s HarmonQuest and Night Train , and Comedy Central’s @midnight all topping the bill. 
Performers at this year’s festival—which runs from March 10 through March 18—include Doug Benson, Jason Mantzoukas, Guy Branum, John Hodgman, Scott Aukerman, Morgan Murphy, Michael Ian Black, Wanda Sykes, and many more. Other notable shows at this year’s festival include live tapings of Comedy Bang Bang! , Harmontown , and Doug Loves Movies , plus an exclusive interview panel with Bob Odenkirk.
